Welcome back to The Daily Courant, your afternoon potluck featuring Puck=E2=
=80=99s best new
reporting.

=C2=A0

First up today, Rachel Strugatz digs into what=E2=80=99s really happening a=
t Glossier as the $1.8 billion beauty brand prepares to launch its third fr=
agrance in just six months=E2=80=94evidence of its success in a high-margin=
 category, perhaps, but also a potential warning signal that the company ne=
eds to grow its revenue, fast, as investors including Sequoia, Thrive, and =
Forerunner
seek an exit strategy.

=C2=A0

Plus, below the fold: Dylan Byers pinpoints the latest source of agita insi=
de CBS as Evening News staffers question leadership=E2=80=99s perceived lig=
ht-touch coverage of Trump. On Wall Street, Bill Cohan scrutinizes the new =
=E2=80=9Cdouble-bonus=E2=80=9D phenomenon spreading through investment bank=
 boardrooms. Leigh Ann Caldwell
chronicles the House G.O.P. quasi-war over Mike Johnson=E2=80=99s =E2=80=9C=
one big beautiful=E2=80=9D budget bill. And in an Inner Circle exclusive, M=
arion Maneker sits down with the top curator of 21c Museum Hotels, Alice Gr=
ay Stites, to examine the commercial logic of =E2=80=9Cliving with art.=E2=
=80=9D

Meanwhile, on The Town, Matt Belloni is joined by entertainment marketing e=
xecutive Terry Press to unpack the
